55	 * message with the sequence number 3 has a predecessor message with the sequence number 2 and a successor message with
56	 * the sequence number 4. The message sequence 2,3,5 has a gap because the successor of 3 is missing. The resequencer
57	 * therefore has to retain message 5 until message 4 arrives (or a timeout occurs).
58	 * <p>
